 as a director of autozone inc from july  to october  contents  early life and education  career  personal life  references  external links early life and educationedit lampert was born in  to dolores lampert and floyd m lampert his mother was a housewife his father was a senior partner in the law firm of lampert  lampert in new york city he has a younger sister tracey lamperts grandmother was a passive investor and big fan of louis rukeysers wall street week television program she instilled in him an interest in investing his mother would later recall that young eddie would sit with his grandmother reviewing and evaluating the performance of her stock picks in the daily newspaper lamperts father died at the age of  and his mother took a job as a clerk at saks fifth avenue his mother would later say eddie really assumed the responsibility knowing that life had changed and we had to accomplish something by ourselves now in order to help support his family eddie worked after school and on weekends at various warehouses stocking shelves and filling orders despite working he earned good grades played both soccer and basketball and won the scholar athlete award at his high school he received financial aid to help pay for college lampert graduated from yale university in  ba economics summa cum laude where he was a member of skull and bones and phi beta kappa careeredit in july  lampert worked as an intern at goldman sachs and then worked in the firms risk arbitrage department from march  to february  while there he worked directly with robert rubin when lampert decided to go out on his own rubin warned him it would be a bad career decision in april  lampert left the bank to form esl investments based in greenwich connecticut the name esl derives from lamperts initials richard rainwater whom lampert had met on nantucket island gave him  million in seed money and introduced him to clients such as david geffen lampert typically holds his investments for several years and usually has between three and fifteen stocks in his portfolio his investment style was once drawing comparisons to the financier warren buffett lamperts earnings in  were estimated to be  billion making him the first wall street financial manager to exceed an income of  billion in a single year in  lampert was featured on the time  list for most influential people in the world for being one of the brightest minds on wall street and leading a new class of activist hedge funds lampert was the richest person in connecticut in  with a net worth of  billion lamperts earnings in  were estimated to be from  to  billion in march  lampert was no  on the forbes world wealthiest people list with a net worth of  billion by august  lampert had fallen to no  on the list with a net worth of  billion in january  it was announced that lampert would take over as chief executive officer at sears after louis dambrosio stepped down due to family health matters which took effect in may  in july  he held  of shares in sears holdings corp worth of approximately  million lampert is an avid follower of ayn rand and has used elements of rands philosophy to guide his business decisions in early  lampert then president chief executive officer and top shareholder of sears holdings was estimated to have personal assets of  billion primarily in the hedge fund esl investments inc early in the year he committed to providing an additional loan of  million to sears and said he would provide letters of credit to sears for additional amounts reportedly totaling  million and possibly increasing to a half billion dollars in the future he has been strongly criticized by employees and corporate staff for shredding his employees in corporate meetings and being out of touch with reality as well as for failing to invest in the physical stores as many of them are deteriorating  personal lifeedit in  he married kinga lampert and they have three children they have homes in indian creek village florida aspen colorado and greenwich connecticut the couple are active members of their local chabad house in  lampert was kidnapped from the parking lot of his greenwich office but was able to convince his captors to let him go after two days of captivity referencesedit  a b c d forbes the worlds billionaires  eddie lampert september   a b c d e f g berner robert november   the next warren buffett businessweek retrieved june     miller james p march   sears chief wont run for autonations board chicago tribune retrieved april     sec filing autozone inc retrieved april     gary r smith is wed to tracey r lampert the new york times april     a b sellers patricia february   eddie lampert the best investor of his generation cnn money   robbins alexandra  secrets of the tomb skull and bones the ivy league and the hidden paths of power little brown and company p    martin patrick  highest wall street pay tops  billion a year retrieved    kadlec daniel  the  time  contenttimecom   the  richest americans connecticut rankings forbescom    mason melvin greenwich home to billionaires on forbes list the greenwich daily voice retrieved  july    edward lampert   smith aaron january   hedge fund manager lampert adds ceo role at sears cnn money retrieved march     lampert edward insider trading insidermolecom retrieved  july    mina kimes at sears eddie lamperts warring divisions model adds to the troubles bloomberg business july    lynn parramore ayn randloving ceo destroys his empire salon december    edward lampert forbes forbes january   retrieved january   took over as sears ceo in   has presided over a remarkable dismantling   sweeney brigid january   with craftsman sale sears takes another step toward the grave chicago business crain communication inc retrieved january   the company may need  billion in cash to get through  amid sales declines and store closures including almost  million in minimum pension contributions   httpwwwbusinessinsidercomsearsfailingstoresclosingedwardlampertbankruptcy